{
  "text": "Rainfall measurements started from 15 May 2012. The measurements were done with a manual rain bucket before 22 July, and thereafter with a tipping bucket rain gauges (TE525WS, Campbell Scientific Inc., Logan, UT, USA) at distances of about 50 m around the tower. All micrometeorological variables were recorded every 30-min by data loggers (CR200X for PPT, CR3000 for all others, Campbell Scientific Inc., USA) from 6 April to 18 October, 2012. LAI was measured by destructive sampling at roughly weekly intervals within a 100 m\u02c6100 m plot centered on the flux tower [CITATION_1] .",
